Task: Implement the GStreamer WebRTC media engine, devices, controls, and statistics

Summary:
- Added an optional GLib-compatible GStreamer 0.23 WebRTC engine with Opus/VP8 send and dynamic receive paths.
- Added hashed GstDeviceMonitor inventory, selection/reconfiguration, mute/camera privacy controls, safe teardown, and bounded statistics conversion.
- Added zeroed/redacted SDP and ICE values plus deterministic synthetic media coverage.

Files:
- Cargo.toml
- Cargo.lock
- src/huddles/mod.rs
- src/huddles/devices.rs
- src/huddles/media.rs

Validation:
- cargo test --locked (461 passed)
- cargo test --locked --features native-media,huddle-harness (462 passed)
- native synthetic GStreamer pipeline smoke test passed with camera disabled until explicit enable

Decisions:
- Generic WebRTC media remains capability-gated and is not claimed as Slack/Chime interoperability.
- Camera sources are locked in NULL before PLAYING and return to NULL when disabled.
- Device identifiers are SHA-256 scoped hashes; SDP/ICE are redacted and zeroed on drop.
